262
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:52,641
"Successful"?

263
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:56,061
Speaking of which,

264
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:00,482
classmates are supposed to
help each other out, right?

265
00:15:00,941 --> 00:15:01,984
Please sign up.

266
00:15:02,818 --> 00:15:04,403
You haven't been listening?

267
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,571
I have no job.

268
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,656
I obviously can't afford insurance.

269
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,575
-Oh, Seo-yeon is here.
-She came?

270
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:11,952
She's a TBC news anchor.

271
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:20,377
I'm sorry I'm late.

272
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,421
Don't worry.

273
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:24,882
Seo-yeon, sit here.

274
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:27,092
Gosh, why are you so heavy?

275
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:28,469
Thank you.

276
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:33,015
-Hi.
-Hi.

277
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:35,059
Hye-ja, have you been well?

278
00:15:35,142 --> 00:15:37,102
-Yes.
-I'm sorry I'm late.

279
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:39,813
Hyeon-jong was advising me
on tomorrow's news program.

280
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:42,024
-I see.
-Anchor Kim Hyeon-jong?

281
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:43,150
Are you close to him?

282
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:44,860
I'm a newcomer.

283
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:47,863
He advises others as well.

284
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:50,115
You totally look like a news anchor
already.

285
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:52,743
No way. This is only my first year.

286
00:15:52,826 --> 00:15:54,870
I can barely find my way
around the broadcasting station.

287
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,247
It's incredible.
You became a TBC news anchor.

288
00:15:58,832 --> 00:16:00,834
Isn't she the first club member
who got into TBC

289
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:02,336
in six years?

290
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:04,380
Is that right?

291
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:11,387
Hye-ja, did you apply for TBC this year?

292
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:14,473
I meant to look for your application,

293
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:17,351
but I've been so busy
meeting different people.

294
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:18,769
It's okay.

295
00:16:19,269 --> 00:16:21,522
I didn't even apply, so don't worry.

296
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:23,315
I've completely given up.

297
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:26,652
Then why are you trying to become
a reporter,

298
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:28,278
going around cities,
getting stung by a wasp,

299
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:30,280
and getting swollen up
after eating lacquered chicken?

300
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:31,865
You haven't given up, am I wrong?

301
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:34,118
You... Stop it.

302
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:36,036
Hye-ja, do you remember?

303
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:39,415
In my freshman year,
you corrected my pronunciation.

304
00:16:40,874 --> 00:16:42,751
You said I had trouble with the S sound,

305
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:45,629
and made me repeat the sentence,
"She sells seashells," many times.

306
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:48,340
"She sells seashells."

307
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:51,260
I guess I still haven't nailed it.

308
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:53,387
Really? Hye-ja did that?

309
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,473
To the future TBC news anchor?

310
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,641
Exactly.

311
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:58,976
I must have been out of my mind.

312
00:16:59,059 --> 00:17:00,269
I didn't know my place.

313
00:17:00,352 --> 00:17:03,480
By the way, from Seo-yeon to Jang-ho,

314
00:17:03,564 --> 00:17:06,817
I'm glad many of our club members
are doing well.

315
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,986
I heard Jang-ho is back in Korea.

316
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:09,903
Really?

317
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,322
He was visiting the director
of the broadcasting station.

318
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:16,201
He really seems to live his life
to the fullest.

319
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:18,328
While working as a TBC news anchor,

320
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:20,456
he saw a photo of a refugee camp,

321
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:23,000
