and became a war correspondent.

322
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:24,877
You didn't ask him to come today?

323
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,004
He said he's going to a family gathering.

324
00:17:27,379 --> 00:17:29,798
But he promised to stop by at next
week's workshop in Ganghwa Island.

325
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:32,593
You'll be there too, right?

326
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:34,470
-Me?
-I think I heard

327
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:37,473
you had a crush on him a long time ago.

328
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:41,477
I wasn't the only one
who had a crush on him.

329
00:17:41,977 --> 00:17:45,272
But you even told him you liked him,

330
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:46,440
if I heard correctly.

331
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:55,115
Yes, I told him I liked him!

332
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:59,203
I didn't exactly get turned down, though.

333
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:02,247
I was just ignored.

334
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:06,210
I don't care about Kwon Jang-ho
or anyone else anymore.

335
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:09,505
I don't need anyone!

336
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:18,597
Gosh.

337
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:22,684
Who are you?

338
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:26,897
What...

339
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,484
Why didn't you make any sound?

340
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:33,237
I didn't want to embarrass you.

341
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:36,532
Are you a pervert or what?

342
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:40,702
Watching other people from a dark place.

343
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:45,749
I came here first.

344
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:50,003
I would have stood up and left,
but that would have humiliated you.

345
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:52,756
So I decided to stay here until you leave.

346
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:55,551
What kind of pervert would think that?

347
00:18:56,218 --> 00:19:00,055
Still, if you noticed
someone was coming here...

348
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:06,061
Gosh, I'm sleepy.

349
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:15,988
Is he homeless?

350
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:17,281
HELP-WANTED

351
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:18,991
Oh, I don't think he is.

352
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:23,453
Gosh, that pervert.

353
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:26,498
He better not show up in front of me.

354
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,418
He didn't exactly look like a pervert.

355
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:33,172
Hey. What makes you think so?

356
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:35,424
He was hiding alone in the park at night

357
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:37,467
and watching you. So which part exactly?

358
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:39,219
It's just my gut feeling.

359
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:42,055
Sorry. The night shift came late.

360
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:44,600
Why do you carry a guitar around
when you can't even play it?

361
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:47,352
Don't be like that. She's a musician.

362
00:19:48,645 --> 00:19:50,397
It just expired.

363
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:54,067
Thank you. You're so smart.

364
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:55,903
Your part-time job isn't what matters.

365
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,654
You said you'd settle things
with your agency.

366
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:59,072
Will they renew your contract?

367
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:00,157
It's already been renewed.

368
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,658
-Really?
-For how much?

369
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:03,952
"How much"? They didn't say how much.

370
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:05,579
-What about your debut?
-My debut?

371
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:07,539
They said I can debut if I want to.

372
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:09,708
It's their job to debut you.

373
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:12,419
So what were the terms?

374
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,924
I can use the practice room
as much as I want.

375
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:19,009
I can come and go as I want,

376
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:21,053
debut as I want,

377
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,847
and decide the duration
of the contract as I want to.

378
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:25,224
So what can you not do as you want?

379
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:29,353
They just don't want me
to tell anyone I belong to them.

380
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,314
What should we do?

381
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:33,482
What should we do with you?

382
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:35,901
You guys wanted my contract to be renewed.

383
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:37,027
Fine, good job.

384
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:39,529
By the way, Hye-ja, where were you?

385
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:41,657
She went to a broadcasting club gathering.

386
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,534
Jang-ho is back in Korea.

387
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:46,036
Who...

388
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,080
The person you drank Kaoliang for?

389
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:51,166
Guys, this is not the right place.

390
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:53,543
-Right?
-Let's go.

391
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:55,587
BANQUET

392
00:20:56,672 --> 00:21:00,217
When he said he was going to be
a war correspondent,

393
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:03,136
I thought he was lying to turn me down.

394
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,471
It just didn't make sense.

395
00:21:04,554 --> 00:21:06,848
Why would a news anchor suddenly
become a war correspondent?

396
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,768
But he had many reasons to turn you down.

397
00:21:09,851 --> 00:21:11,228
You're not going to deny it, are you?

398
00:21:11,311 --> 00:21:13,772
You know you were partly responsible
for me asking him out, don't you?

399
00:21:13,855 --> 00:21:16,191
What are you talking about?
You said you had to get drunk

400
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:18,151
and asked for strong liquor yourself.

401
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:21,196
Right. You mixed Kaoliang wine with beer

402
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,990
and gulped it down.

403
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:35,919
Jang-ho.

404
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:38,005
Why didn't you guys stop me?

405
00:21:39,923 --> 00:21:41,967
Do you know what bothers me the most?

406
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:45,012
The next day, I remembered everything.

407
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:47,889
But he acted as if nothing had happened.

408
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,309
He was a nice guy to the end.

409
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:53,145
You want to see him, don't you?

410
00:21:54,521 --> 00:21:56,440
Just once, no more.

411
00:21:56,523 --> 00:21:58,525
Forget it. If he sees you again,

412
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:00,110
he'll only remember the time you threw up.

413
00:22:00,193 --> 00:22:01,445
I guess you're right.

414
00:22:01,528 --> 00:22:04,740
But I heard all guys have
positive feelings towards

415
00:22:04,823 --> 00:22:06,158
girls who asked them out.

416
00:22:06,241 --> 00:22:07,784
-Is that right?
-Do you think that's right?

417
00:22:07,868 --> 00:22:10,329
If that's right, he would've gone
out with you even if you threw up.

418
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:13,874
That sounds so romantic.

419
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:16,043
Isn't that true love?

420
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,210
You're right.

421
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:19,379
I'm sure there were reasons
why he didn't go out with me.

422
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:22,424
Right. I shouldn't go.

423
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:23,800
I won't go.

424
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:26,219
It'd be too humiliating.

425
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,893
That dropped on the floor earlier.

