512
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,956
We can't waste this food.

513
00:27:50,126 --> 00:27:53,129
Hey, forget it. It's better for me
to gain weight.

514
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:54,339
I'll eat it.

515
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:57,258
By the way, why is Yeong-su
so quiet today?

516
00:27:57,926 --> 00:27:59,010
He came home with pork...

517
00:27:59,969 --> 00:28:01,971
He came home, and he's probably
in his room.

518
00:28:02,597 --> 00:28:04,224
Get him a simple snack.

519
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:06,434
If he doesn't eat at that age,
he'll get sick.

520
00:28:06,976 --> 00:28:08,103
Okay.

521
00:28:25,829 --> 00:28:27,914
Hey. Are you enjoying it?

522
00:28:28,623 --> 00:28:30,625
You even locked the door to eat alone?

523
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:32,460
Did you take kimchi with you?

524
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:36,381
Goodness. He's too busy eating
to hear anything.

525
00:28:44,514 --> 00:28:45,932
Hey, Yeong-su.

526
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:47,976
Is the neighbor grilling pork?

527
00:28:48,226 --> 00:28:50,019
-It smells.
-Yeong-su!

528
00:28:50,395 --> 00:28:51,813
-What?
-What?

529
00:28:53,106 --> 00:28:54,649
This door won't open.

530
00:28:55,024 --> 00:28:58,027
-How much tape did he put on here?
-What tape?

531
00:28:59,112 --> 00:29:00,488
Wait. What's wrong with this door?

532
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:03,867
Hey, Yeong-su. Yeong-su!

533
00:29:04,576 --> 00:29:06,995
You idiot! Open this door now!

534
00:29:07,245 --> 00:29:08,246
Yeong-su!

535
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:10,165
Yeong-su!

536
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:12,709
-Yeong-su.
-Oh, my gosh!

537
00:29:12,917 --> 00:29:15,920
-Yeong-su!
-Yeong-su!

538
00:29:16,212 --> 00:29:17,297
Oh, gosh.

539
00:29:17,714 --> 00:29:18,631
-What do we do?
-Yeong-su!

540
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:20,008
-Yeong-su!
-Yeong-su!

541
00:29:20,425 --> 00:29:21,676
Oh, no...

542
00:29:23,303 --> 00:29:25,722
He temporarily suffocated
due to lack of oxygen.

543
00:29:29,642 --> 00:29:30,727
What?

544
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:32,729
What did you say?

545
00:29:37,901 --> 00:29:38,902
What did he say?

546
00:29:40,695 --> 00:29:43,031
He asked you to flip the pork
so it doesn't get burned.

547
00:29:46,075 --> 00:29:47,202
Sorry?

548
00:29:51,206 --> 00:29:52,832
-Honey.
-No, Mom.

549
00:29:52,916 --> 00:29:54,083
-Mom.
-Get him out of here.

550
00:29:54,167 --> 00:29:55,335
-Hurry up and go!
-Mom.

551
00:29:55,502 --> 00:29:57,170
-Honey.
-Mom, no.

552
00:29:57,253 --> 00:29:59,130
-Mom.
-Let go of me!

553
00:29:59,214 --> 00:30:01,007
-Hey! Stop!
-Honey!

554
00:30:01,090 --> 00:30:03,802
-Honey, come back!
-Mom, no!

555
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:08,598
Gosh. Yeong-su died?

556
00:30:09,015 --> 00:30:10,350
What do you mean?

557
00:30:10,517 --> 00:30:12,727
He didn't die. He wanted to die,

558
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:14,896
so he lit coal inside his room.

559
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:17,649
The ambulance was here,
and it was a total frenzy.

560
00:30:17,732 --> 00:30:19,108
Is it because he was stressed?

561
00:30:19,234 --> 00:30:21,152
Gosh, that's so tragic.

562
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:24,113
Still, he was very fortunate to survive.

563
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:26,908
I heard they smelled the meat
burning from his room.

564
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:29,494
-I hope he wasn't burnt badly.
-I know.

565
00:30:29,577 --> 00:30:31,412
-They talk too much.
-Gosh.

566
00:30:32,664 --> 00:30:34,123
They just make up fake stories.

567
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:37,085
-Hyeon-ju, it's a relief, isn't it?
-What is?

568
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:39,629
Yeong-su was your first love.

569
00:30:39,712 --> 00:30:42,340
Hey, watch that mouth of yours.
Hyeon-ju, wait.

570
00:30:42,423 --> 00:30:45,009
It's all right. We all do

571
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:47,470
crazy things like that once in our lives.

572
00:30:47,554 --> 00:30:48,763
Don't get angry.

573
00:30:48,930 --> 00:30:50,014
You brat.

574
00:30:51,641 --> 00:30:52,642
Hey, Sang-eun.

575
00:30:53,184 --> 00:30:55,395
I'll tell you
one last time, so listen carefully.

576
00:30:55,979 --> 00:30:57,105
Back then...

577
00:30:58,731 --> 00:31:01,651
I didn't know he'd grow up
to be such a loser.

578
00:31:03,194 --> 00:31:04,195
Sit down.

579
00:31:04,279 --> 00:31:05,405
Do you know what my wish is?

580
00:31:06,197 --> 00:31:09,158
It's to get on a time machine
and go back to when I liked him

581
00:31:09,242 --> 00:31:10,410
and pull all my hair out.

582
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:12,036
Hey, we understand. Calm down.

583
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,913
I'll pull out all his hair for you.

584
00:31:14,163 --> 00:31:17,792
Why? Isn't it so courageous
to express how you feel?

585
00:31:17,917 --> 00:31:19,002
-You...
-Hey, don't.

586
00:31:19,836 --> 00:31:21,004
By the way, what about you?

587
00:31:21,796 --> 00:31:23,756
Aren't you going to go meet
that Jang-ho guy?

588
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:25,383
He said he was coming
to the staff training.

589
00:31:26,009 --> 00:31:28,011
Shouldn't you keep participating
in events like that?

590
00:31:29,929 --> 00:31:32,849
Why? Is it because of that elephant
in the field girl or something?

591
00:31:32,932 --> 00:31:34,350
I said she's a deer in the forest.

592
00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:35,977
What on earth is an elephant in the field?

593
00:31:36,185 --> 00:31:38,146
Still, what a bummer.

594
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:41,733
You said Jang-ho lives abroad.

595
00:31:41,816 --> 00:31:43,985
You don't even know
when he will come back.

596
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,405
No. I won't be swayed anymore.

597
00:31:47,488 --> 00:31:49,949
I have to live my life.
Whether it's for work, or for men.

598
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:53,244
-Still, I think you should--
-Forget it!

599
00:31:53,328 --> 00:31:55,663
Although you may feel that way,
but I don't care at all.

600
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,040
So stop it. I'm not going.

601
00:31:57,874 --> 00:32:00,251
I won't live a weak-willed life anymore.

602
00:32:00,793 --> 00:32:03,296
I'll say goodbye to him for good.

603
00:32:14,682 --> 00:32:17,852
I'm just going to see him once
and go back.

604
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:19,312
I'm really going to leave.

605
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:31,282
HAPPY BEAUTY SALON

606
00:32:34,369 --> 00:32:36,579
Hello. What brings you here
so early in the morning?

607
00:32:36,663 --> 00:32:38,539
This is some radish water kimchi.

608
00:32:38,623 --> 00:32:41,292
Radish water kimchi is the best
for curing gas poisoning.

609
00:32:41,501 --> 00:32:43,836
This has been fermented
for more than three years.

610
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:47,840
Once he takes a whiff of this,
he'll be totally cured.

611
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:51,636
-It's not gas poisoning...
-I heard it was coal.

612
00:32:51,928 --> 00:32:55,390
-That's not it. He grilled meat--
-Mr. Kim.

613
00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:59,102
In the old days, they said
the eldest son comes from the sky.

614
00:32:59,185 --> 00:33:02,105
That means he's a very precious person.

615
00:33:02,438 --> 00:33:04,565
I'm not saying this because

616
00:33:05,066 --> 00:33:08,236
I lost my eldest son
during the January–Fourth Retreat.

617
00:33:08,361 --> 00:33:09,529
I see.

618
00:33:09,612 --> 00:33:11,489
You should listen to us, Mr. Kim.

619
00:33:14,784 --> 00:33:15,952
Okay.

620
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:24,961
Where... Where is Hye-ja?

621
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:27,463
She went out early to some school retreat.

622
00:33:28,965 --> 00:33:30,216
Dad.

623
00:33:30,675 --> 00:33:32,593
Can you please take me outside?

624
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:34,679
What?

625
00:33:46,983 --> 00:33:50,194
The lady who lives in the house
with that blue door

626
00:33:50,778 --> 00:33:52,113
brought this for you.

627
00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:57,910
Eat it all.

628
00:33:58,619 --> 00:34:00,329
Do not leave a single drop.

629
00:34:02,915 --> 00:34:03,958
Okay.

630
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:14,427
Gosh.

631
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:17,388
Eating radish water kimchi
makes me crave ribs.

632
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,817
Honey, I'll be outside.

633
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:33,613
Don't come home early.

634
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:35,198
Dad...

635
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:41,162
Dad, Dad.

636
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:43,664
No. It's too much. Mom, please...

637
00:34:51,881 --> 00:34:53,841
Look at them having such a great time.

638
00:34:57,553 --> 00:34:59,639
Thank goodness I have you.

639
00:35:00,973 --> 00:35:03,476
I was so worried,
thinking that I'd be the only oldie.

640
00:35:04,268 --> 00:35:05,228
I know, right?

641
00:35:05,311 --> 00:35:07,396
Thank goodness I have you with me.

642
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:08,523
Right?

643
00:35:09,857 --> 00:35:11,067
What about your kids though?

644
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:12,902
Why do you think I came here?

645
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:15,988
I know the younger ones
are uncomfortable around me,

646
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:19,075
but this is the only
legitimate excuse I have

647
00:35:19,158 --> 00:35:21,035
to enjoy some alone time.

648
00:35:22,578 --> 00:35:24,455
I respect for you.
Raising kids must be so hard.

649
00:35:24,747 --> 00:35:25,832
It sure is.

650
00:35:27,875 --> 00:35:29,418
The real oldie is here.

651
00:35:31,546 --> 00:35:33,422
-Hello.
-Hello.

652
00:35:33,506 --> 00:35:35,049
I heard you work
as a war correspondent now.

653
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:36,801
Did you work in construction
in the Middle East?

654
00:35:36,884 --> 00:35:37,969
You're so tanned.

655
00:35:38,219 --> 00:35:40,096
Hey, I was even more tanned.

656
00:35:40,596 --> 00:35:42,557
I'm sorry I couldn't go to your wedding.

657
00:35:42,723 --> 00:35:44,142
I was covering one of the civil wars.

658
00:35:45,309 --> 00:35:46,477
Have you been well?

659
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:48,104
Yes.

660
00:35:48,187 --> 00:35:49,689
Isn't that Lee Jun-ha
of Hanguk University?

661
00:35:49,772 --> 00:35:51,149
What's he doing here?

662
00:35:51,232 --> 00:35:52,525
Hey, come here.

663
00:35:53,776 --> 00:35:55,945
-This is Lee Jun-ha.
-Yes, I know him.

664
00:35:56,028 --> 00:35:58,197
He's already famous
in the broadcasting industry.

665
00:35:58,406 --> 00:36:02,201
I heard every broadcasting company
wants to hire him as an anchor.

666
00:36:02,326 --> 00:36:05,830
Right, but he wants to be a reporter.
Like me.

667
00:36:05,913 --> 00:36:08,207
I know I wasn't invited. I'm sorry.

668
00:36:08,291 --> 00:36:10,960
Don't be. Handsome guys
are always welcome.

669
00:36:11,252 --> 00:36:13,671
I'm Jang-ho's huge fan.

670
00:36:13,754 --> 00:36:16,174
I pestered him to make time
to meet me when he returns.

671
00:36:17,633 --> 00:36:18,926
I invited him.

672
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:22,346
Everyone here will work in the industry,
so it'll be good to know each other.

673
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:24,390
This is my friend, Kang Ji-yeon.

674
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:28,394
And this is my junior,

675
00:36:28,728 --> 00:36:29,645
Kim Hye-ja.

676
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:31,272
She wants to be a news anchor too.

677
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:33,941
Hello.

678
00:36:34,942 --> 00:36:36,277
Yes, hello.

679
00:36:38,279 --> 00:36:41,240
Well, can I call you by your first name?

680
00:36:41,532 --> 00:36:43,201
Or shall I address you politely?

681
00:36:46,245 --> 00:36:48,456
I'm TBC news anchor, Jang Seo-yeon.

682
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:51,918
Hello.

683
00:36:55,546 --> 00:36:57,131
Elephant in the field.

684
00:37:13,105 --> 00:37:14,815
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

685
00:37:23,532 --> 00:37:24,909
Congratulations on your wedding.

686
00:37:26,577 --> 00:37:28,246
Right, thanks.

687
00:37:29,038 --> 00:37:31,207
My wife unexpectedly got a job offer
from the UN,

688
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:33,876
so we rushed and had a small
ceremony with just our families.

689
00:37:35,086 --> 00:37:36,796
-What about you?
-Sorry?

690
00:37:39,131 --> 00:37:40,258
I'm single.

691
00:37:40,967 --> 00:37:43,344
-You suggested it.
-I know.

692
00:37:45,805 --> 00:37:46,889
Drink up.

693
00:37:47,890 --> 00:37:49,725
Jang-ho, I'll get going.

694
00:37:50,142 --> 00:37:51,769
Why? We haven't had a chance to catch up.

695
00:37:51,852 --> 00:37:53,062
Stay for just one more drink.

696
00:37:54,605 --> 00:37:55,982
Just one more drink, okay?

697
00:37:56,190 --> 00:37:57,358
-Have a seat.
-Sit here.

698
00:38:03,864 --> 00:38:06,117
Then will you go straight to Angola?

699
00:38:06,409 --> 00:38:07,952
Yes, I have to.

700
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:09,954
Is that where you and your wife live?

701
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:17,295
We live in South Africa now,

702
00:38:17,378 --> 00:38:18,713
so it's not that far.

703
00:38:19,422 --> 00:38:20,840
I have to go to Angola to cover a story.

704
00:38:21,173 --> 00:38:24,051
As you probably know, the civil war
is still going on there.

705
00:38:26,387 --> 00:38:29,015
Right, the civil war is still going on.

706
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:32,059
Yes, I saw it on the news.

707
00:38:32,810 --> 00:38:35,271
I saw all the tanks and guns.

708
00:38:46,324 --> 00:38:49,118
Since you're saying you have to
get going, I should let you go.

709
00:38:49,452 --> 00:38:50,911
Let me know when you pass the test.

710
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:52,371
-I'll be off, then.
-Okay.

711
00:38:52,455 --> 00:38:53,956
-Go back inside.
-All right.

712
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:02,173
I guess you're leaving.

713
00:39:03,215 --> 00:39:04,550
Yes, I have to take care of something.

714
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:05,968
I see.

715
00:39:07,970 --> 00:39:09,180
Goodbye, then.

716
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:12,224
Wait.

717
00:39:29,658 --> 00:39:31,118
Do you really want to be a news anchor?

718
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,454
Sorry?

719
00:39:34,538 --> 00:39:35,998
Why do you want to be a news anchor?

720
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:41,921
To inform the public of the truth and...

721
00:39:42,088 --> 00:39:43,672
Reporters can do that too.

722
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:47,635
But reporters are...

723
00:39:47,718 --> 00:39:48,928
What? Reporters

724
00:39:49,345 --> 00:39:50,513
aren't cool?

725
00:39:50,930 --> 00:39:53,766
So you want to be a news anchor

726
00:39:54,016 --> 00:39:54,850
because it looks cool?

727
00:39:55,643 --> 00:39:56,685
I feel

728
00:39:57,186 --> 00:40:00,231
as if I'm at an interview
for a news anchor position.

729
00:40:05,152 --> 00:40:06,904
Then have you ever been out on the field?

730
00:40:07,613 --> 00:40:09,865
-What?
-Have you ever been on the field?

731
00:40:10,241 --> 00:40:13,119
I'm not talking about what you can
learn from the answer sheets.

732
00:40:13,369 --> 00:40:16,956
Have you been out on the field
to write the story you'll read?

733
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:20,292
Have you ever experienced
how intense things can get?

734
00:40:20,835 --> 00:40:23,629
Why are you asking me these questions?

735
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:28,217
I want to know what kind of effort
you're making to be a news anchor.

736
00:40:28,717 --> 00:40:31,345
Well, I don't think,

737
00:40:32,054 --> 00:40:34,014
I'm obligated

738
00:40:35,015 --> 00:40:38,144
to answer these questions you're asking.

739
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:41,105
Of course, you don't have to
answer my questions.

740
00:40:41,981 --> 00:40:45,693
But you should be able to answer
these questions for yourself.

741
00:40:48,779 --> 00:40:51,198
I'm talking about the qualifications
you need to pass the exam.

742
00:40:51,699 --> 00:40:54,326
Jang-ho said you're his junior,

743
00:40:55,161 --> 00:40:57,538
whom he's especially fond of.

744
00:41:05,588 --> 00:41:07,965
Stop crying already.

745
00:41:18,684 --> 00:41:20,019
Oh, boy.

746
00:41:20,102 --> 00:41:22,521
BEAUTY SALON

747
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:25,649
My gosh.

748
00:41:25,983 --> 00:41:28,194
Why are you here so early?

749
00:41:28,402 --> 00:41:30,279
I haven't even had breakfast yet.

750
00:41:30,362 --> 00:41:32,239
You can do my hair
after you eat your breakfast.

751
00:41:32,990 --> 00:41:34,825
Okay, I'll quickly have
some rice with soup.

752
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:36,118
-Wait here, okay?
-All right.

753
00:41:38,829 --> 00:41:39,955
Did you skip breakfast again?

754
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:42,958
Gosh, don't worry. My stomach has shrunk,

755
00:41:43,042 --> 00:41:45,711
so I never get hungry
even if I don't eat anything.

756
00:41:47,838 --> 00:41:49,131
Do you want to join me?

757
00:41:49,298 --> 00:41:51,717
There are no side dishes as I didn't
go grocery shopping yesterday.

758
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:54,887
Water and kimchi are all I need.

759
00:41:54,970 --> 00:41:58,390
Even though my mother-in-law
hated me so much,

760
00:41:58,474 --> 00:42:01,185
she said she liked the fact
that I'm not a picky eater.

761
00:42:01,268 --> 00:42:02,269
I'm serious.

762
00:42:02,353 --> 00:42:03,562
Let's go in.

763
00:42:03,646 --> 00:42:06,315
-Hey, you're back.
-You're getting in just now?

764
00:42:06,398 --> 00:42:08,734
Did you stay up all night? My gosh.

765
00:42:09,109 --> 00:42:10,945
Will she get married soon or what?

766
00:42:12,154 --> 00:42:13,864
You can watch TV.

767
00:42:17,618 --> 00:42:18,661
Can I come in?

768
00:42:19,411 --> 00:42:20,829
I'm going to sleep.

769
00:42:26,210 --> 00:42:28,045
Has everyone who came to the reunion

770
00:42:28,837 --> 00:42:30,631
already established a successful career?

771
00:42:32,007 --> 00:42:33,551
You didn't know that before the reunion?

772
00:42:34,385 --> 00:42:37,846
This world is full of people who are
a lot more competent than you.

773
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,723
Will you cry every single time
you encounter them?

774
00:42:39,807 --> 00:42:42,142
Starving yourself and lying in bed
won't solve anything.

775
00:42:42,726 --> 00:42:44,186
It won't solve any of your problems.

776
00:42:46,522 --> 00:42:47,731
What happened?

777
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:52,444
Do you know the difference between
being competent and living a good life?

778
00:42:52,611 --> 00:42:55,531
Even if you're incompetent,
just get in there

779
00:42:56,115 --> 00:42:57,324
and tell the world, "I'm here.

780
00:42:58,284 --> 00:42:59,952
I want to give hope to the likes of me."

781
00:43:00,035 --> 00:43:01,745
That is how you live a truly good life.

782
00:43:03,706 --> 00:43:05,583
As for competence,
you must be born with it,

783
00:43:06,125 --> 00:43:08,043
but you can live a good life
