me to a job.

1028
00:57:18,977 --> 00:57:20,728
You should use this for yourself.

1029
00:57:20,812 --> 00:57:22,689
That shampoo sink is broken.

1030
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:24,065
It isn't much,

1031
00:57:24,232 --> 00:57:26,651
but I'd feel better if I can pitch in.

1032
00:57:28,027 --> 00:57:31,114
I never imagined receiving money
from my child.

1033
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:34,951
-Are you happy?
-Of course I am.

1034
00:57:35,201 --> 00:57:37,996
Oh, gosh. You did a great job, Hye-ja.

1035
00:57:41,666 --> 00:57:43,209
Okay, Dad.

1036
00:57:43,293 --> 00:57:45,086
Next time I make money,
it will be all yours.

1037
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:46,296
Okay?

1038
00:57:47,005 --> 00:57:48,047
Eat this.

1039
00:57:48,131 --> 00:57:49,299
What is it?

1040
00:57:49,799 --> 00:57:51,176
Red bean buns!

1041
00:57:58,641 --> 00:58:00,518
I'm the one who always brings her stuff,

1042
00:58:00,602 --> 00:58:03,104
but you always take the credit.

1043
00:58:03,438 --> 00:58:05,773
She promised she'd make money
and buy me a new taxi.

1044
00:58:07,442 --> 00:58:09,861
Whether she keeps her promise
or not, I'm so proud of her.

1045
00:58:10,820 --> 00:58:12,947
She is our daughter so she knows
how hard we work.

1046
00:58:14,616 --> 00:58:16,993
I can't use this money.

1047
00:58:17,327 --> 00:58:19,871
It's like our daughter's first paycheck.

1048
00:58:21,915 --> 00:58:22,957
I can't use this.

1049
00:59:10,964 --> 00:59:12,882
Okay. I'll have some udon

1050
00:59:12,966 --> 00:59:15,802
and a half bottle of soju,
and forget everything.

1051
00:59:16,844 --> 00:59:17,971
Then I'll go to sleep.

1052
00:59:18,221 --> 00:59:20,640
MIDNIGHT SNACK BAR

1053
00:59:23,017 --> 00:59:25,144
Sir, I'll have a soju and a udon.

1054
00:59:28,231 --> 00:59:30,942
I didn't mean to...

1055
00:59:35,446 --> 00:59:37,073
Sir, I won't need the soju.

1056
00:59:43,913 --> 00:59:45,123
That was...

1057
00:59:58,052 --> 00:59:59,846
not what I wanted...

1058
01:00:11,190 --> 01:00:14,319
Sir. Give me another bottle of soju.

1059
01:00:14,402 --> 01:00:15,320
Yes.

1060
01:00:15,403 --> 01:00:16,487
One more bottle.

1061
01:00:24,412 --> 01:00:25,955
The guy who wants to be a reporter?

1062
01:00:26,581 --> 01:00:28,041
What brings you to our neighborhood?

1063
01:00:30,126 --> 01:00:32,295
We already knew we live
in the same neighborhood.

1064
01:00:33,338 --> 01:00:36,799
Oh, that's right. How stupid of me.

1065
01:00:36,924 --> 01:00:38,301
You're a resident in this area.

1066
01:00:39,218 --> 01:00:40,303
I see.

1067
01:00:43,222 --> 01:00:46,476
Although you're not rich, I thought
you were from a nice family.

1068
01:00:46,976 --> 01:00:48,853
But you're filthy broke like me.

1069
01:00:50,521 --> 01:00:51,522
But it's strange.

1070
01:00:51,606 --> 01:00:53,941
Broke people usually recognize each other.

1071
01:00:55,109 --> 01:00:56,653
It's because I'm even more broke than you.

1072
01:00:56,819 --> 01:00:58,196
There's a class between broke people.

1073
01:00:58,279 --> 01:01:00,114
Come on, don't be silly.

1074
01:01:00,406 --> 01:01:02,909
You may think our beauty salon
belongs to my family,

1075
01:01:02,992 --> 01:01:05,161
but it belongs to the bank.
We owe them a debt.

1076
01:01:05,244 --> 01:01:07,246
And it's not a small amount.

1077
01:01:07,330 --> 01:01:09,290
It's serious. It's "debt" in English.

1078
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:10,833
The "B" is a silent syllable.

1079
01:01:11,584 --> 01:01:13,127
Is this a battle to see
who is more pitiful?

1080
01:01:13,211 --> 01:01:15,129
I'm confident I can beat anyone.

1081
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:19,258
My mom's middle finger
on her right hand is bent

1082
01:01:19,384 --> 01:01:20,968
because she's held the scissors
for so long.

1083
01:01:22,387 --> 01:01:24,055
My grandma doesn't have
any fingerprints left

1084
01:01:24,138 --> 01:01:25,807
because she has worked so much.

1085
01:01:29,727 --> 01:01:33,022
I'm talking about my mom.
Why bring your grandma into this?

1086
01:01:33,106 --> 01:01:35,692
What should I do then?
I don't have a mom or a dad.

1087
01:01:35,775 --> 01:01:37,902
My mom ran away when I was young,
and my dad

1088
01:01:39,278 --> 01:01:41,406
is someone I wish who doesn't
exist in this world.

1089
01:01:48,287 --> 01:01:50,081
Sir, give us another bottle of soju.

1090
01:01:52,083 --> 01:01:53,126
I lost.

1091
01:01:55,670 --> 01:01:57,338
-Here.
-Thank you.

1092
01:01:59,841 --> 01:02:00,883
Wait!

1093
01:02:01,175 --> 01:02:02,218
Give it to me.

1094
01:02:12,103 --> 01:02:13,146
Here.

1095
01:02:16,983 --> 01:02:18,943
So after I grew up,

1096
01:02:20,987 --> 01:02:23,197
I've never been able to relax.

1097
01:02:24,991 --> 01:02:27,952
I did everything to earn money.

1098
01:02:29,036 --> 01:02:30,913
Even though I should be preparing
for the exam now,

1099
01:02:31,873 --> 01:02:34,542
I still take on construction jobs
and even work in other cities.

1100
01:02:44,927 --> 01:02:47,180
My story is too depressing
and boring, right?

1101
01:02:51,476 --> 01:02:55,813
But I must say, it sounds like
you've been doing your very best.

1102
01:02:57,648 --> 01:03:00,943
I have no confidence,

1103
01:03:02,737 --> 01:03:04,739
and I don't even know what to do.

1104
01:03:06,365 --> 01:03:07,533
To tell you the truth,

1105
01:03:08,409 --> 01:03:10,536
except for a few times at the beginning,

1106
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:13,206
I've never even sent my resume
to broadcasting stations.

1107
01:03:16,918 --> 01:03:19,337
Failing a few interviews

1108
01:03:20,213 --> 01:03:22,757
gave me a reality check.

1109
01:03:23,007 --> 01:03:25,968
Even during the interviews,
the interviewers

1110
01:03:26,385 --> 01:03:29,180
did ask me some questions,
but I could tell

1111
01:03:29,972 --> 01:03:33,601
whether or not they were asking them
just to be polite.

1112
01:03:35,019 --> 01:03:37,104
For strong candidates,
all interviewers, right off the bat,

1113
01:03:38,606 --> 01:03:39,857
smile at them.

1114
01:03:40,775 --> 01:03:43,402
What they say doesn't even matter.

1115
01:03:44,862 --> 01:03:48,157
But even I don't think I qualify

1116
01:03:49,992 --> 01:03:51,244
as a strong candidate.

1117
01:03:53,496 --> 01:03:56,457
I'm a little lame.

1118
01:03:59,961 --> 01:04:02,713
But at the same time, it's so hard.

1119
01:04:03,089 --> 01:04:05,424
to come to terms with it
and just accept it.

1120
01:04:07,260 --> 01:04:09,637
Why? It's because...

1121
01:04:11,806 --> 01:04:13,724
I care about myself a great deal.

1122
01:04:15,560 --> 01:04:18,813
I really want myself to do well,

1123
01:04:20,815 --> 01:04:23,860
but this girl is a little... She's lame.

1124
01:04:32,076 --> 01:04:35,162
Now, I certainly know
that I'm not cut out for it,

1125
01:04:36,205 --> 01:04:38,791
but I don't have the courage
to give it all up.

1126
01:04:39,292 --> 01:04:42,336
If I give this up,
I'll need a different goal.

1127
01:04:42,420 --> 01:04:45,089
But I'm so scared that I might
never achieve that goal.

1128
01:04:49,176 --> 01:04:50,887
Gosh, had I known I'd end up like this,

1129
01:04:51,387 --> 01:04:54,140
I would've never decided
to become a news anchor

1130
01:04:55,516 --> 01:04:57,894
and just worked hard
like you've been doing.

1131
01:04:59,770 --> 01:05:03,566
Then I would've at least
earned some money.

1132
01:05:05,443 --> 01:05:08,779
Then my parents
wouldn't have had to work so hard.

1133
01:05:11,282 --> 01:05:12,366
Do you regret your decision?

1134
01:05:14,368 --> 01:05:17,246
Yes. I really regret

1135
01:05:18,623 --> 01:05:21,042
deciding to become a news anchor.

1136
01:05:22,335 --> 01:05:24,337
If I never set that goal for myself,

1137
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:27,006
I think I'd be much happier now.

1138
01:05:28,257 --> 01:05:30,760
I want to go back to that point in time.

1139
01:05:30,968 --> 01:05:33,721
I want to go back in time
and tell myself to give up on that dream.

1140
01:05:33,804 --> 01:05:35,348
I really want to do that.

1141
01:05:37,767 --> 01:05:39,727
I, too, would love to go back in time.

1142
01:05:43,689 --> 01:05:44,899
What if you could?

1143
01:05:46,192 --> 01:05:48,736
If you could actually turn back time,

1144
01:05:50,404 --> 01:05:51,781
what would you do?

1145
01:05:55,618 --> 01:05:56,744
I won't go to my grandma.

1146
01:06:00,081 --> 01:06:02,208
I'd rather live at an orphanage.

1147
01:06:04,085 --> 01:06:05,378
I won't live with my grandma.

1148
01:06:06,671 --> 01:06:09,924
I'd never let her take me in
and suffer that misery again.

1149
01:06:28,776 --> 01:06:29,902
Gosh.

1150
01:06:32,071 --> 01:06:33,447
That's heart-wrenching.

1151
01:06:36,951 --> 01:06:40,663
-Yes, don't let her suffer again.
-Here.

1152
01:06:44,709 --> 01:06:45,751
Let's go home.

1153
01:06:46,711 --> 01:06:47,795
All right.

1154
01:06:48,170 --> 01:06:50,256
This isn't an easy decision for me,

1155
01:06:50,339 --> 01:06:52,591
but I'll grant you an opportunity
to change things.

1156
01:06:53,009 --> 01:06:54,260
What opportunity?

1157
01:06:55,636 --> 01:06:58,597
How did you know I brought this today?

1158
01:07:01,058 --> 01:07:02,893
The opportunity to turn back time.

1159
01:07:09,650 --> 01:07:11,068
My gosh.

1160
01:07:13,571 --> 01:07:14,947
It'd be so nice if it were true.

1161
01:07:15,281 --> 01:07:16,490
It is true.

1162
01:07:17,450 --> 01:07:18,868
It's possible.

1163
01:07:19,618 --> 01:07:21,162
I mean, I can't make it happen,

1164
01:07:22,371 --> 01:07:24,248
-but this watch can.
-Sure.

1165
01:07:24,331 --> 01:07:26,459
-Do you really want to do it?
-Yes, I really do.

1166
01:07:27,084 --> 01:07:28,252
Do you really want it?

1167
01:07:28,544 --> 01:07:31,047
-Show me. Go ahead.
-You're serious, right?

1168
01:07:31,839 --> 01:07:33,674
Don't regret later.

1169
01:07:34,050 --> 01:07:36,135
Once it's done, there's no going back.

1170
01:07:36,260 --> 01:07:37,511
Okay, show me.

1171
01:07:58,824 --> 01:08:00,993
SPECIAL THANKS TO HYUN-WOO, KIM KI-RI

1172
01:08:13,923 --> 01:08:14,965
Thank you

1173
01:08:15,049 --> 01:08:17,134
for your offer to turn back time for me.

1174
01:08:17,218 --> 01:08:19,303
Let's try to be more generous,
talk casually to each other.

1175
01:08:19,386 --> 01:08:21,972
Considering what we went through,
we should be talking casually.

1176
01:08:22,181 --> 01:08:24,350
That's how love begins.

1177
01:08:24,767 --> 01:08:27,311
He was hit by a truck as he was
making a left at an intersection.

1178
01:08:27,561 --> 01:08:29,855
Please...

1179
01:08:33,776 --> 01:08:35,986
Ma'am, what is your name?

1180
01:08:36,070 --> 01:08:37,154
I'm Kim Hye-ja.

1181
01:08:37,321 --> 01:08:40,908
Mom and Dad, you still can't tell
that I'm your daughter?

1182
01:08:41,450 --> 01:08:42,993
This is the only way.

1183
01:08:43,077 --> 01:08:45,371
Dad, mom. I'm sorry.

1184
01:08:46,122 --> 01:08:48,124
